		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon">
					<img src="http://www.ronpaulforums.com/images/icons/icon1.png" alt="Default" /> 
				</h2>
				


						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_4719090">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							First, lots of phone calls from collection agencies. And I mean LOTS. First one agency, then when they give up, another.<br />
<br />
Next, threatening letters from collection agencies.<br />
<br />
If the amount is high enough, they can sue. Sometimes in small claims, sometimes not. If they win, the judge can require you to pay. I've never heard of wages being garnished for credit card debt, but I suppose it might be possible in some states.<br />
<br />
I believe some cards have terms that allow repossession of things you bought with the card if you don't pay, but most are unsecured.<br />
<br />
Tip: if you ever decide to pay after a long period of not paying, never pay the collection agency. Only pay the original owner of the debt, even if they have subsequently sold it to others for collection. Much less damage to your credit score that way, and the collection agencies don't get as much of a cut, if any.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
                                       
                                 
				
		        		<blockquote class="signature restore"><div class="signaturecontainer">My blog: <a href="http://www.12knowmore.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">www.12knowmore.com</a><br />
&quot;You can ignore reality, but you can't ignore the consequences of ignoring reality.&quot; -- Ayn Rand</div></blockquote>
				
                                        
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
