						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							if it's not a huge amount they'll simply try to harass you into paying it<br />
<br />
if it's enough money they'll sell it to a lawyer who will sue you for it<br />
<br />
however, obtaining a judgment and actually being able to collect it are two distinct things<br />
<br />
you can wait it out 10 years or declare bankruptcy as a means of discharging it - eventually it will be written off and that will be that<br />
<br />
if you intend not to pay, don't communicate with any collection agencies, that will reset the clock on the account
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
